[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Samuel said to Saul, “I was the one the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " sent to anoint you as king over his people Israel. Now listen to what the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " says."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Here is what the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of hosts says: ‘I carefully observed how the Amalekites opposed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Israel along the way when Israel"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " came up from Egypt. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So go now and strike down the Amalekites. Destroy everything that they have. Don’t spare"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " them. Put them to death – man, woman, child, infant, ox, sheep, camel, and donkey alike.’” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So Saul assembled"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the army"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and mustered them at Telaim. There were 200,000 foot soldiers and 10,000 men of Judah. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Saul proceeded to the city"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of Amalek, where he set an ambush"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in the wadi."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Saul said to the Kenites, “Go on and leave! Go down from among the Amalekites! Otherwise I will sweep you away"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " with them! After all, you were kind to all the Israelites when they came up from Egypt.” So the Kenites withdrew from among the Amalekites."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Saul struck down the Amalekites all the way from Havilah to"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Shur, which is next to Egypt. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He captured King Agag of the Amalekites alive, but he executed all Agag’s people"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " with the sword. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " However, Saul and the army spared Agag, along with the best of the flock, the cattle, the fatlings,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and the lambs, as well as everything else that was of value."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They were not willing to slaughter them. But they did slaughter everything that was despised"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and worthless."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then the word of the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " came to Samuel: "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “I regret that I have made Saul king, for he has turned away from me and has not done what I told him to do.” Samuel became angry and he cried out to the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " all that night."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Samuel got up early to meet Saul the next morning. But Samuel was informed, “Saul has gone to Carmel where"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " he is setting up a monument for himself. Then Samuel left"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and went down to Gilgal.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When Samuel came to him,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Saul said to him, “May the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " bless you! I have done what the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " said.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Samuel replied, “If that is the case,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " then what is this sound of sheep in my ears and the sound of cattle that I hear?” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Saul said, “They were brought"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " from the Amalekites; the army spared the best of the flocks and cattle to sacrifice to the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " our God. But everything else we slaughtered.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Samuel said to Saul, “Wait a minute!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Let me tell you what the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " said to me last night.” Saul"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " said to him, “Tell me.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Samuel said, “Is it not true that when you were insignificant in your own eyes, you became head of the tribes of Israel? The "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " chose"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " you as king over Israel. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " sent you on a campaign"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " saying, ‘Go and exterminate those sinful Amalekites! Fight against them until you"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " have destroyed them.’ "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Why haven’t you obeyed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "? Instead you have greedily rushed upon the plunder! You have done what is wrong in the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "’s estimation.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Saul said to Samuel, “But I have obeyed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "! I went on the campaign"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " sent me on. I brought back King Agag of the Amalekites after exterminating the Amalekites. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But the army took from the plunder some of the sheep and cattle – the best of what was to be slaughtered – to sacrifice to the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your God in Gilgal.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Samuel said, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“Does the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " take pleasure in burnt offerings and sacrifices"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "as much as he does in obedience?"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Certainly,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " obedience"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " is better than sacrifice;"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "paying attention is better than"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the fat of rams."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For rebellion is like the sin of divination,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "and presumption is like the evil of idolatry."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Because you have rejected the word of the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ","
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "he has rejected you as"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " king.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Saul said to Samuel, “I have sinned, for I have disobeyed what the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " commanded"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and what you said as well."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For I was afraid of the army, and I followed their wishes."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now please forgive my sin! Go back with me so I can worship"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ".”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Samuel said to Saul, “I will not go back with you, for you have rejected the word of the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", and the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has rejected you from being king over Israel!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When Samuel turned to leave, Saul"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " grabbed the edge of his robe and it tore. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Samuel said to him, “The "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has torn the kingdom of Israel from you this day and has given it to one of your colleagues who is better than you! "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The Preeminent One"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of Israel does not go back on his word"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " or change his mind, for he is not a human being who changes his mind.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Saul"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " again replied, “I have sinned. But please honor me before the elders of my people and before Israel. Go back with me so I may worship the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your God.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So Samuel followed Saul back, and Saul worshiped the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Samuel said, “Bring me King Agag of the Amalekites.” So Agag came to him trembling,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " thinking to himself,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Surely death is bitter!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Samuel said, “Just as your sword left women childless, so your mother will be the most bereaved among women!” Then Samuel hacked Agag to pieces there in Gilgal before the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ". "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Samuel went to Ramah, while Saul went up to his home in Gibeah of Saul. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Until the day he"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " died Samuel did not see Saul again. Samuel did, however, mourn for Saul, but the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " regretted that he had made Saul king over Israel."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]